{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 46656719, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "SOCPL-2024-INFO-REPR", "title": "Information, consultation & participation of representatives of undertakings", "publicationDateLong": 1704931200000, "callIdentifier": "SOCPL-2024-INFO-REPR", "callTitle": "Information, consultation & participation of representatives of undertakings", "callccm2Id": 46656749, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43252517, "abbreviation": "SOCPL", "description": "Social Prerogative and Specific Competencies Lines (SOCPL)"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43252542, "abbreviation": "SOCPL-1-1", "description": "SOCPL-1-1"}], "topicMGAs": [], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "SOCPL-PJG SOCPL Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43251093, "abbreviation": "SOCPL-AG", "description": "SOCPL Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "11 January 2024", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["19 March 2024"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3510301": [{"action": "SOCPL-2024-INFO-REPR - SOCPL-PJG SOCPL Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "11 January 2024", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["19 March 2024"], "budgetYearMap": {"2024": 2500000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2024"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">ExpectedOutcome</SPAN>:<p>The main objective of this call is to develop employees\u2019 involvement in undertakings by raising awareness and contributing to the application of European Union law and policies in this area, against the background of the twin transition and changes that it triggers in the world of work, and, in particular, the take-up and effective functioning of European Works Councils.</p>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<p>Actions to promote European level and stregthened transnational cooperation between social partners that address the following themes would be expected:</p><ul level=\"0\"><li>to promote exchange and wider dissemination of knowledge and good practices and to launch actions aimed <strong>at supporting the setting up and good functioning of </strong><strong>European Works Councils.</strong></li><li>to support workers\u2019 involvement in the anticipation and management of change and the prevention and resolution of disputes in the event of various forms of restructuring in EU level undertakings and groups of undertakings, <strong>as required to address challenges brought by the implementation of the European Green Deal</strong> (cf.Council recommendation of 16 June 2022 on ensuring a fair transition towards climate neutrality),<strong> and by the digital transformation of economies </strong>(e.g. impact of Artificial Intelligence (AI) on work organisation or working conditions)<strong>.</strong></li> </ul>\n", "conditions": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:-.55pt;line-height:normal\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&#10;&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;&#10;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligible countries</span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;&#10;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">:&nbsp;as described in the Call document.</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:&#10;justify;text-indent:-.55pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\">EU Member States and in some cases from the European Economic Area (EEA) countries, in accordance with the EEA Agreement.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligibility and admissibility conditions:</span></b><span style=\"font-size:&#10;12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&#10;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"> as described in the Call document.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"> </span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-style:italic\">Applications must be submitted before the <b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">call deadline </b>and <b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">electronically</b> via the Funding &amp; Tenders Portal Electronic Submission System.</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"> Paper submissions are NOT possible.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Text1\" style=\"margin-left:0cm;tab-stops:36.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:&#10;12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-style:italic\">Applications (including annexes and supporting documents) must be submitted using the forms provided <i>inside</i> the Submission System.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Body\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;line-height:14.0pt\"><span class=\"Hy